A lot of twists and deaths. I feel like:
The movie opened up as if it was going to be the best starwars ever filmed. It was so anticipated that when it was over I really felt confused.

The high wore off once the action stopped. it was so mellow everyone in the theater could hear me eat popcorn and open my fruit snacks.

I felt like I was watching a bunch of pathetic outcasts struggle to survive let alone rebel against anyone. This movie was about watching the worst two days in the galaxies existence. I would of rather watch maz barfight instead of the rebels trying to escape and then die.

I don't know why but this isn't the same starwars I spent most my life dreaming about. This was a shit movie filled with meaningless dialog.
